Today we honor those brave men & women who made the ultimate sacrifice 🙏🏼🇺🇸❤️⁣
⁣
I know Murph is the traditional Memorial Day workout, but if you’re looking to mix it up, give this one a try! ⁣Wait til the end to screenshot the workout description 📱📸⁣
⁣
I named it Battle of the Bulge in honor of the third-biggest military campaign in American history (but whose name is also a good description of the workout itself). The reps are in reference to the dates of the campaign, which began on 12/16/44 and ended with an Allied victory on 1/28/45. ⁣
⁣
This is a full-body workout, but you only do one burpee per round because 𝙛𝙧𝙚𝙚𝙙𝙤𝙢 🇺🇸💪🏼⁣
⁣
One thing to keep in mind as you do this workout: Allied Forces were outnumbered and outgunned in the Battle of the Bulge. German forces had more men, more tanks, and more weapons. It would have been really easy to justify sitting that one out, but America didn’t. They went over there and they kicked some Axis ass. I’m sure they were scared- terrified, probably- but they fought anyway. Keep that in mind the next time you’re afraid to fail. Do it anyway. ⁣
⁣

📢 Announcement! Coming August 1 I’ll be releasing The 30/40/50 Method, a training and nutrition program designed just for women in their (you guessed it) 30s, 40s, and 50s 😎 ⁣
⁣
After working directly with these women for the last 8+ years (and being one myself), I’ve noticed that the vast majority of us aren’t getting the results we want, even if we are training hard and our diet is on point. ⁣
⁣
Turns out, women need to take other things into consideration when they try to reach their health & fitness goals. (As I’m sure you’ve found out by now, nature doesn’t make things easy for us females 🙄)⁣
⁣
I’ve also discovered that the majority of our struggles come from hormone imbalances and gut health issues. The 30/40/50 Method is designed to help every woman figure out exactly what their body needs to get back into balance through nutrition, supplementation, and, of course, exercise. ⁣
⁣
And rest assured, this ain’t your grandma’s training program. Just because we’re older doesn’t mean we need to tone down our workouts. The 30/40/50 Method will have the same killer workouts I’ve been posting on my @heatherblackfit page for the last several years. ⁣
⁣
The 30/40/50 Method will have several training options:⁣
no-equipment workouts⁣
barbell and dumbbell strength programs⁣
20- to 30-minute HIIT workouts⁣
core & butt-focused program⁣
extra credit cardio⁣
⁣
And so much more! Stay tuned for more info 😃 ⁣
⁣

You can continue to feel sorry for yourself. ⁣
⁣
You can find reasons why you can’t get what you want.⁣
⁣
You can justify your action or inaction. ⁣
⁣
But feelings and reasons can also be excuses that keep us stuck.⁣
⁣
You can let your circumstances destroy you, or you can use them as fuel for your transformation.⁣
⁣
In that first photo I was heartbroken, and for what most would consider a pretty damn good reason. But I soon realized I had a choice to make. I could let these feelings ruin me, or I could make something really f*cking great out of them. ⁣
⁣
And 9 years later, here we are. ⁣
⁣
That painful path provides perspective. It allows me to help others who also feel sad, broken, and hopeless. And there’s nothing better than seeing the light in their eyes as they are becoming the person they never imagined they could be ❤️ ⁣
⁣
📸 @gregglc

🤔 Right or left? 🤔⁣
⁣
Got on the scale yesterday for the first time in forever, and it was heavier than I anticipated. At first I was in shock, but after a while I realized I wasn’t practicing what I preach to my clients every day.⁣
⁣
Instead of looking at the number on the scale, measure your progress by asking these questions:⁣
⁣
▪️ How do you feel in your clothes?⁣
▪️ How do you feel when you’re naked?⁣
▪️ Are you lifting heavier weight than before?⁣
▪️ Have you achieved any of your fitness goals (first pull up, more unbroken push ups, etc.)⁣
▪️ Are other aspects of your life (mood, sleep, sex drive, energy) improving?⁣
⁣
If you don’t like the number on the scale but can answer “yes” to the above questions, then keep doing what you’re doing! ⁣
⁣
If you answered “no,” then it might be time to take a look at your diet, exercise routine, water intake, sleep quality, etc. to see how we can improve. ⁣
⁣
As for me, the picture on the left was when I was a lot weaker than I am now, both physically and mentally. The girl on the left wanted a big strong butt where there was no butt at all. The girl on the right lifts heavier and feels better than ever before. ⁣
⁣
